<h2 id="download--installation">Download &amp; Installation</h2>
<p>To download and install Visual Studio Code, follow the directions here:</p>
<ul>
  <li>https://code.visualstudio.com/download</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p>In this course, we will develop our code using Visual Studio Code.  In addition, we will organize our code in <strong>project</strong> folders, which will helps us keep our code organized and tidy.  A project folder will contain all of the necessary files for the project’s website.</p>

<p>Visual studio makes it easy to create and work on <strong>projects</strong>:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Make a new folder on your computer using Windows Explorer or the Finder for MacOS and give it a your project title.</li>
  <li>From Visual Studio Code, select File-&gt;Open</li>
  <li>Browse to your project folder, and then click “open”.
<img src="/assets/img/module1/vscode_project1.png" alt="" /></li>
  <li>You will see all of the files you’ve created for your project on the left hand side-bar.
<img src="/assets/img/module1/vscode_project2.png" alt="" /></li>
  <li>You can view the code for any file on the right hand side.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="happy-editing">Happy Editing!</h2>

